item.title: Looook here =]
item.dc:creator: @iceyfang iceyfang
item.description:
@iceyfang wrote:

you have to
open the port(you said you have, but ill make sure you know how) by going to firewall and add port then fill in the info.
portforward. go to www.portforward.com and find your router on the list, then follow the step by step instructions, it’s really easy.
go to www.no-ip.org or www.no-ip.com i forget which, and im too lazy to figure out. then create an account (everything is free don’t freak out) and click manage on the left side. click add once you see it. fill in your server name and put what you want after it, like tjifdsghfkd.no-ip.org/biz/info.
then make sure your comp recognizes java by following "god of ikiliki"s guide on how to create a server.
then get a source(you have one but some dont) then run it.
then try to log in by using your acc details then as the server name type
127.0.0.1
that is your personal ip(i forget what it’s called).
then, if it lets you log in, log out and try to log in using your actual server name(ex. gftwscape.no-ip.org)

hope this helps :S
